               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490702-name-504" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-504" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-504" type="surname" value="HARE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-504" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH HARE</persName>
                  </hi>. On 23d June, I was in Lower Marsh—Ball spoke to me, and I missed this handkerchief (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>), which was in my pocket about three minutes before—I saw a person running, who I believe was the prisoner—I followed him—I lost sight of him for about three seconds, behind some boarding—I came up to him again, and told him to hand over my handker<lb></lb>chief, which he did, and ran away—he was stopped in the York-road.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490702-name-505" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-505" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-505" type="surname" value="VAUGHAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490702-name-505" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGK VAUGHAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker. I saw the prisoner take the hand<lb></lb>kerchief from Hare's pocket, and called his attention to it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Where were you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> In the shop—I was looking out of the door—I am not aware that anybody was standing between you and I—there was another one with you, a party walking behind you.</p>
